   The formula pattern (compatible with LibreOffice) is:
   ```
   =IFERROR(INDEX(SORT(UNIQUE($H$2:$H${max_row})),COLUMNS($Q$2:Q2)),"")
   ```
   – `SORT(UNIQUE(...))` creates a sorted list of distinct values.  
   – `INDEX(..., COLUMNS($Q$2:Q2))` picks the 1st, 2nd, … element as the formula is copied across columns.  
   – `IFERROR(...,"")` returns a blank when there are fewer than 6 unique values.
